    "actions_taken": [
      "Job shut down and all required parties notified",
      "ROV sent to inspect A004 jumper for damages",
      "Tree and A004 jumper recovered from seafloor on Feb 23, 2014",
      "A004 hub secured with high pressure cap and pressure tested to 7500 psi",
      "A004 jumper sent for refurbishment",
      "BOPs latched and well work resumed after safety determination"
    ],
    "summary": "On January 2, 2014, while pulling the subsea tree from Marubeni's A002 well, the Tree Retrieving Tool (TRT) inadvertently released from the tree and fell to the seafloor, damaging the A004 well's jumper. The incident resulted from failure to properly verify TRT latch before lift-off, inadequate surface testing procedures, misinterpretation of safe zone positioning, and failure to perform required over-pull tests.",
